CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Couier Newspaper June 25, 1941 reads: "Participated In Local Golf Tournament - Above are shown four of the participants in the Elks' Western Pennsylvania Open Golf Tournament and also their trophies.  From left to right they are: Peter Dillard, chairman; Eldridge Wilson, second in the first flight score; Dave Wilson, first with a score of 4; and Gene Scott, second in the second flight, Earl Gray, first in the second flight, is not pictured.  Attendance was good and enthusiasm was high all during the tournament. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of four men, participants in the Elks' Western Pennsylvania Open Golf Tournament, left to right, Peter Dillard, Eldridge Wilson, Dave Wilson, and Gene Scott, standing in Harris Studio with circular background and trophy table
